criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age: 0 to 6 months;

          -  Subject with cow's milk protein allergy (any clinical signs or symptoms of the skin,
             gastrointestinal tract, respiratory tract or comfortable tract)

          -  Unable to breastfeed;

          -  Vital signs are stable;

          -  Legal guardian has signed the informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Subject with congenital and hereditary metabolic diseases;

          -  Digestive tract obstruction;

          -  Subject with immunodeficiency diseases;

          -  Subject who is allergic to known components of amino acid formula powder;

          -  The investigator judges it is not suitable for the subject to participate in this
             study.
